--- OVERVIEW: scripts ---

General-purpose helper scripts used throughout the ArcaNN/CP2K/LAMMPS workflow, split into
python/ and bash/. See the root README.md for the full repository map.

--- scripts/python/ ---

o energy_grep.py: reads CP2K energy output files from multiple replica directories, converts
  kinetic and potential energies from atomic units to kcal/mol, and plots the total-energy
  distribution as a histogram. Run from the parent directory containing the replica
  subdirectories.

o extract.py: extracts individual configurations from a multi-frame XYZ trajectory and writes
  them out separately (or as a subsampled trajectory). Validates the frame count and atom
  count, and writes a debug log (debug.txt). Usage: python3 extract.py <trajectory.xyz> <natoms>

--- scripts/bash/ ---

o check_convergence.sh: iterates over CP2K labeling job directories and classifies each
  calculation as converged, not converged (SCF/Cholesky failure), needing manual inspection,
  or missing output; writes a summary report. Run from the labeling iteration directory.

o check_data.sh: validates the presence and consistency of expected data files across the
  labeling dataset directories.

o check_distance.sh: scans candidate configurations for atomic overlaps (inter-atomic
  distances below threshold) that would cause a DFT single-point to fail.

o energy_chart.sh: loops over CP2K replica directories, extracts the total energy per frame,
  and consolidates them into a single all_energies_long.dat file for plotting.

o energy_grep.sh: extracts energy data from LAMMPS/DeePMD run logs across multiple
  simulation directories.

o generate_xyz.sh: converts LAMMPS trajectory (or other) formats to XYZ for visualization
  and further analysis.

o job_lammps-deepmd.sh: SLURM submission wrapper for LAMMPS+DeePMD exploration runs;
  sets up modules/environment and launches the LAMMPS executable.

o python_submission.sh: SLURM wrapper for submitting Python analysis scripts to the cluster
  queue.

Note: this README was written to give a general overview of pre-existing content; no
existing file in this tree was modified to produce it.
